To expand his power, Napoleon used these assassination plots to justify the creation of an imperial system based on the Roman model. He believed that a Bourbon restoration would be more difficult if his family's succession was entrenched in the constitution.[113] Launching yet another referendum, Napoleon was elected as Emperor of the French by a tally exceeding 99%.[96] As with the Life Consulate two years earlier, this referendum produced heavy participation, bringing out almost 3.6Â million voters to the polls.[96]
